Speaker learn is an app we are desigining to be a professional music and speaker equalizing platform. 
Its goal is to make all speakers sounds the same based on user preferences (with resepect to hardware limitations)

It begins be having the user test their speaker as follows: 
    -The speaker should be connected to your device
    -The user can select from queried connected audio devices
    -There will be five test audios (a button connected to each sound): 
        1. A sound that is pure bass
        2. A sound that is pure mids
        3. A sound that is pure treble
        4. A sound that is all three
        5. A sound that is a mix of known troublesome frequencies
    -Each audio will be played on the local device speakers (if they are detected), then played on the speaker.
    -They will rate the volume of the tone on 5 point scale (3 being same volume as local device speakers)
    -They will rate the quality of the tone by selected the tone and designating if it was good or bad
    -After all five tones have been played and rated, the app will calculate the optimal EQ settings for the speaker, flattening the frequency response as much as possible and compensating troublesome frequencies.
    -The app will then play a test tone with the optimal EQ settings for the user to listen to. And a short clip of music with the optimal EQ settings for the user to listen to.
    -
    
    The user can then adjust the EQ settings to their liking.
    -The app will save the EQ settings for the speaker. And auto configure the device to play at those configs.
    -The user can then select from queried connected audio devices
    -The user will then be able to create a custom profile for their speakrer. This profile will be used to adjust the EQ settings for the speaker to their personal preferences for what their audio should sound like with resepect to the device's quality and baseline volume constraints.
    

